tweet: 6 vessels moving Sun; 1 salt, 5 US with grain, coal, limestone and scrap iron. 7 on Mon including McCarthy, PaulR, Isle, Beeghly and more
The Walter J. McCarthy, Jr. left Duluth at 10am on Thanksgiving with coal to be discharged at Essexville and then St. Clair.
The barge Innovation arrived Duluth today, pushed by the tug Samuel de Champlain. Together, they are 543 feet long; they brought cement.
The American Century left Duluth today with 64,000 tons of coal for Ontario Power Generation. She will return  next Wed for more coal.
